::DarkMouse::

She smiled as Quickstrike put her arm around him. She whispered to 
him."Thank you commander."  
She walked back to her console and got the chair.  She brought it 
over to Quickstrike so he could sit down.  She said in a little 
louder voice, just above a whisper. "As you commanded, your chair 
commander."
She held the chair for him, slightly smiling. Once he sat down, she 
would feel a little better.  The drug hadn't kicked in all the way 
and when it did,he would feel 100 feet tall and Lazar proof.
